The original question asked for the exponent and mantissa, rather than the fractional and whole part.

To get the exponent and mantissa from a double you can convert it into the [IEEE 754][1] representation and extract the bits like this:

    long bits = Double.doubleToLongBits(3.25);
        
    boolean isNegative = (bits &amp; 0x8000000000000000L) != 0; 
    long exponent      = (bits &amp; 0x7ff0000000000000L) &gt;&gt; 52;
    long mantissa      =  bits &amp; 0x000fffffffffffffL;


  [1]: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEEE_754

