Use [JSTL][1] ([installation instructions here][2]) [fmt][3] taglib. There&#39;s a [`&lt;fmt:formatNumber&gt;`][4] tag which does exactly what you want and in a quite easy manner with help of `maxFractionDigits` and `maxIntegerDigits` attributes. 

Here&#39;s an [MCVE][5], just copy&#39;n&#39;paste&#39;n&#39;run it.
```xml
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;%@ taglib uri=&quot;jakarta.tags.fmt&quot; prefix=&quot;fmt&quot; %&gt;
&lt;%
    // Just for quick prototyping. Don&#39;t do this in real! Use servlet/javabean.
    double d = 3.25;
    request.setAttribute(&quot;d&quot;, d);
%&gt;
&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    &lt;head&gt;
        &lt;title&gt;SO question 343584&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;/head&gt;
    &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Whole: &lt;fmt:formatNumber value=&quot;${d}&quot; maxFractionDigits=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Fraction: &lt;fmt:formatNumber value=&quot;${d}&quot; maxIntegerDigits=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
```
&lt;sub&gt;*(NOTE: if you&#39;re not on JSTL 3.0+ yet, use `uri=&quot;http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/fmt&quot;` instead)*&lt;/sub&gt;

Output:

&gt; Whole: 3
&gt; 
&gt; Fraction: .25

