`UI2` should be a [dialog](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/components/dialog.html) and not another `JFrame` since *Swing* applications should usually only have a single, [top-level container](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/components/toplevel.html).

You also don&#39;t need to do all the hard work yourself of placing GUI components on the screen nor sizing them. You should use [layout managers](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/layout/index.html) and other, relevant parts of the rich, [API](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20566772/java-jbutton-only-image) &amp;ndash; in order to make the `JButton` look like an app icon.

More notes after the code.
